Florida mailman Doug Hughes landed his gyro-copter on the US Capitol lawn on Wednesday afternoon . 
  House Homeland Security Chairman Michael McCaul said that Capitol authorities were prepared to shoot him down . 
  Hughes claims he informed the Secret Service and Capitol police of his flight . 
  He was flying the craft to raise awareness for campaign finance reform and government corruption . 
  The 61-year-old said he was planning the flight for two years . 
  He landed the craft on the West Front lawn of the Capitol building in Washington D . 
 C . 
  Hughes was arrested after he breached the no-fly zone . 
  The Capitol was in lockdown for several hours . 
 